<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="414" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,361,532]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,361,387]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Prescutum without prescutal and tuberculate pits. Wing with R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1027,1035,380,394]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">1</subScript>
erect at tip, erect part sometimes indistinct; R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[290,298,416,430]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">3</subScript>
very short, at most 1/4 length of R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[696,704,416,430]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">4</subScript>
, basal half erect like crossvein; M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1094,1119,416,430]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">1+2</subScript>
not forked. Legs with tibial spurs absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="414" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,361,532]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,470,496]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Remarks.</emphasis>
This genus includes seven species (
<specimenCount box="[722,773,470,496]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" type="generic">1 sp.</specimenCount>
in the Palaearctic, 2 spp. in the Neoptropical, and 4 spp. in the Oriental Regions) (
<bibRefCitation author="Oosterbroek, P." box="[407,614,506,532]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" refId="ref10528" refString="Oosterbroek, P. (2021) Catalogue of the Craneflies of the World (Diptera, Tipuloidea, Pediciidae, Limoniidae, Cylindrotomidae, Tipulidae). Available from: https: // ccw. naturalis. nl / index. php (accessed 7 September 2021)" type="url" year="2021">Oosterbroek 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
